AB  - This paper concerns employment problem for female college students and the way to conquer it in China. Female college students in China are less likely to be given a good job when compared to their male counterparts after graduation. The reasons include social prejudice against women, which has lasted for thousands of years in China; tensions in the overall employment situation; employer benefit; traditional university education mode; and female college students' own weaknesses. Interventions to alleviate this situation include changing of traditional concept on gender stereotypes, which is fundamental to achieve equality between men and women in employment; issuing of governmental policies against prejudice, which is the most powerful weapon to eliminate gender discrimination in employment; changing of employment concept by employer, from "male better" to a better understanding of women's value; and self-improvement by female students, which means female students should overcome sense of inferiority, and eliminate psychological discrimination themselves.
